article.headline: Incarnate Word rolls over A&M-International 105-83
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Denzel Livingston, who hit 4 of 7 from beyond the arc, had 29 points and Jontrell Walker added 26 as Incarnate Word rolled over Div. II Texas A&M-International 105-83 on Monday night. Kyle Hittle contributed 22 points as he nailed 4 of 5 3-pointers. Walker made 6 of 9 3-point attempts as the Cardinals hit 15 of 25 long range attempts (60%). IWU (4-0) made 33 of 53 field goal attempts (62.3%). Shawn Johnson had six blocks and eight rebounds. A&M-International trailed 29-28 with 6:00 remaining in the first half. IWU scored 16 unanswered points to jump out to a 45-28 advantage with 2:17 remaining in the first half and led 51-34 at the break. Vadal Faniel had 23 points, Montrice McKnight added 16 and Jamie Farrie and David Horst had 12 apiece for the Falcons.
